data.title: Service very nice, breakfast fair
data.text: We visited C Street on a Tuesday morning a little after 9:30 am for breakfast.  Service by the owner was fast and very nice. Coffee was served hot and it was good.  I ordered a scrambled egg  with cheese, bacon, toast and grits.  The eggs were good but no cheese. Bacon was good but would have been better if it was thicker slices.  Toast was hot and buttered.  Don't waste you time and order grits. They tasted like instant out of the pkg with no added flavor and were lumpy.  We would go back if we are in the area but a little more attention to the order would go a long way to make this a special place in a refurbished downtown Hanceville building.

data.title: Live music and a desert
data.text: we were walking bye after eating dinner on our way for the wife to have an ice cream. She heard the local  live musician's and suggested we go in and in we went. once the desert counter caught her eye we ordered a slice of limoncello cake and a cappuccino and they were both perfect. The music was relaxing ... i'm surprised this place wasnt busier !!!

data.title: AWESOME COFFEE HOUSE!!  Comfortable, great coffee & deserts, excellent Tea, wonderful staff!
data.text: This place is wonderful!  The have quality coffee and tea, in-house deserts, fresh food, but most of all a great, earthy, comfy, easy-going atmosphere.   The staff is VERY helpful and friendly.  On Saturday evenings they have local live music (usually great guitarist).  A GREAT place to snack, work, read, hang out - a bit of a haven from the outside.  Very reasonable prices.  The staff is joyfully accommodating, the couches are very comfortable, the entire place is cozy and delightful.

data.title: Ran in to to Get Coffee...
data.text: Service is not very good. They did not help me immediately even though I was the only one in there. They didn't welcome me in either. Just stood there staring at me.

data.title: Easter Breakfast
data.text: Very good breakfast sandwich and coffee. Relaxing on Clematis St. The staff was polite, the food came fast and they played great Indie Rock and Alternative music.

data.title: This place is a rare gem.
data.text: Food is excellent. One of the few places that uses premium ingredients. The coffee is great and they have their own pastry chef from what I can tell. There was an open mic the night I went and It's amazing to see so much community in a store. I came in because 104.3 The Shark rated it the best coffee shop in SoFla. I didn't expect it to be this good or feel this much like home. Not to mention the guys and girls there are really cute and classy. I'll be coming here to work every day when able, great place to hang out and have fun.

data.title: Favorite West Palm Beach Coffee Bar!
data.text: An amazing place to relax, and they have the absolutely best lattes! The people who work there are friendly and they have great events with good live music.

data.title: Amazing Cafe
data.text: I believe this is one of the rising stars this past year. I love this place's staff, and it is the place to go anytime. They have good coffee, some amazing food options, and lots of spaces to use. I've never been to a coffee place that brings you your order wherever you are seated. There are some pretty neat music showcases I need to get to on weeknights. I have friends who've shared their great events! They also have a great student discount, so make sure you ask fellow students! Love it.

data.title: Great atmosphere!
data.text: I like spending time in coffee shops and this had a very cool atmosphere to hang out in downtown and had a really good breakfast as well

data.title: Coffee Yum
data.text: I normally just grab coffee to go here, but last weekend my sister and I ordered in and had omelette switch out coffee. Very good food and coffee. Also, a great atmosphere.

data.title: great place!
data.text: really good & healthy breakfast and lunch options. comfy seating. fresh & clean. this place is a gem! Im here 2-3 times per week and love it!

data.title: Good coffee, not so great food.
data.text:
After reading all the great reviews including one by the Palm Beach Post, I had decided that this would be a good place to celebrate Mother's Day with a nice breakfast. I was disappointed from the moment I walked in.  The breakfast menu is very minimal, which you order at the counter and then find a table.  Yes, the coffee was good but I was really hoping for a great breakfast.
Good thing there weren't that many people there as there are very few tables.  I ordered the French Toast.
It tasted like it came out of a box.  It came with fruit which tasted old.  The bacon was horrible.  I like my bacon tasty, juicy and slightly crunchy.  This bacon was paper thin, dried out and tasted burned.
I even asked what kind of bacon it was because it did not taste like anything I have ever tasted.  My husband ordered an omelet which he liked.  My child ordered an egg and cheese sandwich which she seemed to enjoy.  I guess this is an OK place for coffee.  Maybe the lunch food is better.  I'll stick with First Watch and Nick's Diner for breakfast.

data.title: Great salads, coffees, smoothies, etc!! Something for everyone!! WONDERFUL owners!
data.text: Our daughter took us to C Street, telling us we would love it and she was right!! It's a great little cafe -- very inviting with delicious food. The owner personally made us our salads and told us he will soon start to have live entertainment on Monday nights. This place will remind you of a NYC deli and it's just amazing. They aim to please and make the salads to order while you pick out the toppings you want. The desserts looked AMAZING also, so it'd be a great late night location to come out to and hang out and get coffee and dessert if you didn't want a bar atmosphere. Don't miss this gem!!

data.title: An excellent alternative
data.text:
We were looking for an alternative for S........s and found one! Admittedly, they didn't seem so organised behind the counter, but the variety of products were much better, especially in food,
Space and friendliness. MUCH better ! 
Glad we found it and their fare, a little bit dark on the inside, but an excellent alternative.

data.title: C Street in WPB
data.text: We have been eating at C Street since they opened a few months ago and love it!  It reminds us on a NYC cafe in WPB.  Great food, coffee and service. Very nice owners that make you feel welcome.  Try it out and you will enjoy!

data.title: A relaxing coffee and a fresh omlette.
data.text:
If you happen to be lucky enough to be on the road in West Palm Beach and you need a clean place to grab some coffee/tea and a quick healthy bite, then the C Cafe is your place.  
I came here by accident last night around 9pm and had some tea and enjoyed the leather chairs and free wifi.  Then had a break in the morning and didn't want to wait around in my hotel, so packed up my office and brought it to the C Cafe.  People are friendly, and it's really what a Euro style cafe is all about. Great ambiance inside, and if you have prefer to sit outside, you get a seat on the sidewalk to watch the people stroll by.  
I had an omelette as well which was delicious.  
I tip my hat to the management for such a great spot, and only wish every place I went had a small quaint little cafe like this.  
Also much quieter than the starbucks down the street.

data.title: the best coffee in wpb
data.text:
I recently discovered C Street and I haven't been to Sbux since.
The coffee is the best, the muffins and baked goods taste like they are home made.
The staff are very friendly and eager to please. The only drawback is the café is a little dark but very comfy.

data.title: Quiet and cool
data.text: As good as the competition (the s word) but with a local charm and quiet variety of fresh food. The kids and I found it a nice place to relax and cool down while cruising downtown.

data.title: A Bit of Paris on Clematis
data.text: The C Street Cafe is new to town  and yet it feels like it's always been here. We came for breakfast and loved every bite---we shared 2 delicious thick slab French Toast as well as an omelet for which you can select a variety of items---meats, cheese, veg. All very tasty and the coffee was superlative. The room is large, muted tones reminiscent of a Paris cafe and the large wall mural of an autumn leaf strewn paris park with benches echoed a real bench in the room. There are many cozy seating groups throughout the cafe with a variety of furniture. We were impressed with the friendly staff, great food and ambiance. Vive La C Street  Cafe!

data.title: buenisimo!!
data.text: voy alli con mi esposo y amigos y pasamos una tarde divina! la atencion es buena, aunque es un cafe venden vinos y los sandwish son increiblemente buenos! esta en plena zona donde la diversion y la alegria brillan, clematis se llama la calle que llega hasta la marina, se los recomiendo a todos, lo mismo para estudiar q para alternar con amigos, al lado hay un bar q los domingos se pone buenisimo!!!!
